---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy | Kevin Astuhuaman"
  description="Privacy practices for Kevin Astuhuaman's recruiting portfolio and public-corpus assistant."
  path="/privacy/"
>
  <header class="page-hero privacy-hero">
    <div class="section-shell">
      <p class="eyebrow">Privacy</p>
      <h1>Measure the portfolio, not the person reading it.</h1>
      <p class="lede">A narrow analytics footprint supports recruiter-path decisions without collecting assistant questions or creating a persistent profile.</p>
    </div>
  </header>

  <article class="reading-shell section-pad prose">
    <h2>What is measured</h2>
    <p>Page views and a small set of commands are sent to PostHog: resume downloads, assistant opens, contact clicks, and outbound links. Events can include the page path and explicit UTM source, medium, or campaign values.</p>

    <h2>What is not measured</h2>
    <p>The portfolio analytics client does not send assistant question text, form text, resume lens selections, email content, application history, or Trackly user data. It does not set a persistent analytics cookie. A random identifier lasts for the current browser tab when session storage is available.</p>

    <h2>Control</h2>
    <p>Global Privacy Control and browser Do Not Track signals disable the portfolio analytics client. Blocking the analytics request does not change any page, resume, or assistant functionality.</p>

    <h2>Public assistant</h2>
    <p>Chat sends the current question and up to six prior messages to a separate public endpoint only after the visitor selects Ask. It retrieves evidence from the published public corpus and may use an Azure-hosted language model to synthesize a plain-text answer; the deterministic public-corpus endpoint remains the fallback. Chat never queries Trackly accounts or private user data. Conversation history stays in the current browser tab, and questions, history, answers, and recruiter-identifying information are not stored in portfolio analytics, application logs, or a database.</p>
    <p>Voice is opt-in. Only after the visitor selects Start voice call and grants microphone permission, microphone audio is sent over an encrypted WebRTC connection to the Azure-hosted Realtime service for the live conversation. The portfolio does not display or retain a transcript or audio recording. It records only limited lifecycle metadata such as session identifiers, state, duration, token usage, end reason, and failure category. Ending the call, switching to Chat, hiding the page, reaching the five-minute limit, or encountering a failure closes the connection and releases the microphone.</p>

    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <p>Questions about this policy can be sent to <a href="mailto:kevin.astuhuaman@berkeley.edu">kevin.astuhuaman@berkeley.edu</a>.</p>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .privacy-hero { background: #26362f; }
  .prose { background: white; }
</style>
